-------**Technologies Used for professional React application**---------
HTML5 - Markup

CSS3 - for styling & look n feel.

Less - programmable/ compilable css

bootstrap/foundation - CSS framework
              - MF- RWD (mobile first responsive web-design)

COOKIES should not be used.
session storage/locale storage  API (provided by HTML5) - Client side data storage

WebWorker - Async Javascript
Web Sockets - Push based communication channel / duplex communication - helps to avoid polling @ server side.
2 new protocols: WS - Web Socket,  WSS - Web Socket Secure

Node packages- server side Dev tools/support

NPM - resuable node packages repository. 

Yarn - alternative to npm.

VSCode/Sublime/Webstorm - Javscript IDE

ES6 - Mordern JS OO lnaguage

Babel - Es6 transpiler

React - App development library for views

Redux - App state management

React.Router - Navigation library for react projects

Redux.Thunk - Async actions on Application state with redux

Jest - Unit testing api for react

Jest Mock - mocking library for react components.

Fetch API - simpleified and promises supported ajax libarary

Istanbul - code coverage for React App

ES6Lint - code quality (static code analysis)

JSDoc - javascript documentation framework

JsDocGenerator - document generator.

BrowserSync - live reload of built apps

WebPack - Bundler

Webpack Watch - Automatic bundler when file system changes.

Chrome - Browser

Express - node.js rest framework for debug or web application framework

Scoket IO - websocket server side api

JWT - json web tocken API. (authentication)

Electron - React based application as desktop App. React native application.


